<a name="20"><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><td width=500><p><b>Re: NYC to privatize worst schools</b> <font face=Arial,Helvetica size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by <a href="mailto:wea@takethisout.allmax.com">JohnGalt</a> <b>(wea@takethisout.allmax.com)</b> on Tuesday, August 01 @ 13:33:52 EDT<br>(<a href="user.php3?op=userinfo&uname=JohnGalt">User Info</a>) <a href="http://www.allmax.com/wea/" target="window">http://www.allmax.com/wea/</a> </font></td></tr><tr><td>There's a Colorado proposal to "charterize" non-performing schools. I'm agin' it.<br>
<br>
Charter schools are just another way to sneakily governmentalize private education.<br>
<br>
Instead of charterizing schools, do what New York City is doing, and sell all the Government Indoctrination Centers to private owners.<br>
<br>
After all, we don't have "public" grocery stores, "public" clothing stores, "public" shoe stores, "public" computer stores or "public" car dealers. Why should we have "public" education?<br>
<br>
Look at the quality of the "public" stores that we saw in the former Soviet Union and you'll see exactly why "public" education is a tragically failed experiment in social engineering.</td></tr></table><br><p><font face=Arial,Helvetica size=2 color=000000> [ <a href="comments.php3?op=Reply&pid=20&sid=19&mode=&order=&thold=">Reply</a> ]</font><p></ul><hr noshade size=1></p>
